# A same-line trailing `//` comment after a call argument. In the
# call-argument context the parser attaches the comment at Position=1
# (PosPrefix), Line=true on the argument's outermost node, uniformly for
# every argument kind - unlike the list-element context, where it uses
# trailing positions. For argument kinds whose renderer treats a
# PosPrefix comment as interior content (the nodeManagesInteriorComments
# set: BinaryExpr, StructLit, ListLit) this used to push the comment
# mid-expression or inside the brackets. We lift it to the argument's
# trailing-comment column instead, so it aligns with sibling arguments
# and the argument stays on one line.
#
# This covers each affected renderer path: binaryExprPrec (a + b, x == y),
# chainGroupArms (the multi-arm m | n | o disjunction - the shape of the
# original issue 4403 report), StructLit / ListLit arguments, and a
# conjunction with a non-empty bracket arm.
#
# An EMPTY `{}`/`[]` is the one case the parser cannot disambiguate: a
# trailing comment (after `}`) and a header (after `{`) collapse to the
# same node and RelPos, since there is no inner element to anchor a
# header to. We tell them apart by comparing the comment's source offset
# to the closing bracket: `t & {}` (comment after `}`) lifts, while
# `u & { ... }` (comment after `{`) stays interior.
#
# The RelPos-stripped (programmatic) rendering keeps each comment on its
# own line / inside the brackets: stripping clears the same-line (Line)
# signal, so the comment is treated as own-line content rather than
# lifted. (A genuinely programmatic AST that sets Line without source
# offsets instead falls back to the lifted `t & {}, // c` form.)
-- in.cue --
args: matchN(
	a + b, // arithmetic
	x == y, // comparison
	m | n | o, // multi-arm disjunction chain
	{aa: 1}, // struct arg
	[1, 2, 3], // list arg
	p & {q: 1}, // conj, non-empty struct arm
	t & {}, // conj, EMPTY arm: trailing (comment after })
	u & { // conj, EMPTY arm: interior (comment after {)
	},
)
-- out/relpos --
args: matchN(
	a + b,      // arithmetic
	x == y,     // comparison
	m | n | o,  // multi-arm disjunction chain
	{aa: 1},    // struct arg
	[1, 2, 3],  // list arg
	p & {q: 1}, // conj, non-empty struct arm
	t & {},     // conj, EMPTY arm: trailing (comment after })
	u & { // conj, EMPTY arm: interior (comment after {)
	},
)
-- out/norelpos --
args: matchN(
	a +
		// arithmetic
		b,
	x ==
		// comparison
		y,
	m |
		n |
		// multi-arm disjunction chain
		o,
	{
		// struct arg
		aa: 1
	}, [
		// list arg
		1,
		2,
		3,
	],
	p & {
		// conj, non-empty struct arm
		q: 1
	},
	t & {
		// conj, EMPTY arm: trailing (comment after })
	},
	u & {
		// conj, EMPTY arm: interior (comment after {)
	},
)
